ACT:
 Maharashtra Agricultural Lands (Ceiling on Holdings) Act, 1961, as it stood prior to amendment of Chapters II and III by the Maharashtra Act 21 of 1975-Locus standi of former landlords to file an appeal under the Act-Construction of non-analogous statutes, applying the doctrine of stare decisis, explained-Scope of section 21 as to dropping of the proceedings if death occurs of a person holding on the appointed day land in excess of the ceiling area prescribed in the Act, after filing the return and before a notification containing the declaration regarding surplus land held by him is published in the Official Gazette under section 21 of the Act and possession of such surplus land is taken over by the authorities concerned, explained.
 
